Longest Subarray:

def longsubarr(arr):
    seen = set()
    max_sub = 0
    curr_sub = 0
    left = 0
    for i in range(len(arr)):
        while arr[i] in seen:
            seen.remove(arr[left])
            left += 1
        seen.add(arr[i])
        max_sub = max(max_sub,i-left+1)
    return [max_sub,i,left]
print(longsubarr("abcabcbbmnlgf"))

🧠 Sliding Window – 1 Page Cheat Sheet
🔹 When to Use Sliding Window

Use it when:

Contiguous subarray / substring
Optimize from O(N²) → O(N)
Keywords:
“longest / shortest”
“subarray / substring”
“at most / at least K”
“sum / distinct / replace / frequency”
🔹 Core Idea

Instead of recomputing:

Reuse previous window
→ Add next element
→ Remove outgoing element
🔹 Template 1: Fixed Window (Size = K)
🧩 Use When:
Subarray of exact size K
Example: max sum, average

def fixed_window(arr, k):
    window_sum = 0
    window_start = 0
    result = 0

    for window_end in range(len(arr)):
        window_sum += arr[window_end]

        if window_end >= k - 1:
            result = max(result, window_sum)  # or process
            window_sum -= arr[window_start]
            window_start += 1

    return result

